8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 282, L.D. 598, “An Act to Require
10 Minimum Pay for Reporting to Work”
11 Amend the bill in section 2 in §639-A in subsection 3 in the last line (page 1, line 29
12 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "duties." the following: 'If the employer does not
13 have any duties to assign to the employee, the employer shall pay the employee the wages
14 under subsection 2.'
15 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
16 number to read consecutively.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, stipulates that if there
1199 are no duties for an employer to assign to an employee who reports to work as a result of
2200 not receiving notice not to report to work, the employer must pay the employee the wages
2211 required by the bill for an employee who reports to work at the request of the employer and
2222 whose shift is cancelled or reduced.
